Tan ABSTRACT The tracer study assessed post graduation outcomes of BSEd Mathematics students from the University of the Philippines Dilan 1 analyzed ther employment rate, job satisfaction, and pursuit of graduate studies. Results indicate that most are now teaching in secondary schools or working in curriculum, development roles. A minority pursued data analytics careers. Graduates cited the UP academic environment as both challenging and rewarding. The findings suggest that mathematical modeling and statistics courses are highly beneficial in non teaching professions. However, a gap remains in exposure to classroom technology.
